Subject:[arin-announce] The NRO supports the "Stop the Net Grab" campaign
Today the Number Resource Organization (NRO) expressed support for the
"Stop the Net Grab" campaign spearheaded by the International Trade
Union Confederation (ITUC) and Greenpeace International.

"Stop the Net Grab" was launched in response to the restrictive
proposals that will be considered at the upcoming World Conference on
International Telecommunication (WCIT-12).

More about "Stop the Net Grab":

http://www.change.org/petitions/stop-the-net-grab

ARIN, as part of the NRO, shares these concerns and emphasizes the
importance of the multi-stakeholder Internet governance model.

For more information, please refer to the NRO statement:

http://www.nro.net/news/nro-shares-concerns-aboutwcit-process


Regards,

Communication and Member Services
American Registry for Internet Numbers (ARIN)



